definitions.definition: The suburbs as a whole and all that characterizes or pertains to them; ( sometimes derogatory ) the suburbs as encapsulated or represented by the typical characteristics or qualities of the people living there, especially complacency , conformity , conservativeness , dullness , etc.

main_definition: ( originally British ) The suburbs as a whole and all that characterizes or pertains to them; ( sometimes derogatory ) the suburbs as encapsulated or represented by the typical characteristics or qualities of the people living there, especially complacency , conformity , conservativeness , dullness , etc. [from late 19th c.]
